k provides rich resources for those who wish to explore faith and belief in complex social circumstances, either as research or as community engagement. In such increasingly divided times, work like this is needed now more than ever.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aRELIGION / Faith.2bisacsh1 aHickey-Moody, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526165251zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526165251zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526165251/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-MUPb2023